children.subject: Cool! When can we expect the redesign to be completed?
What if they're cool, berkeley things but lack people? :)
hi all, we need photos again! Please send us your photos.

history.content:
Hello! I think most of you have heard, we are doing a major professional redesign of the EECS website. We've heard your feedback that our current website is too text-heavy, and we need your help! Many of you are amazing photographers, part of cool clubs and projects. We need your beautiful photographs to use on our website. Please send us your photos of hack-a-thons, study groups, social outings, research, and other amazing things that you all do to news@eecs.berkeley.edu.
 
Legal stuff, we do need release forms from students if they are clearly recognizable in the photograph (group photos excepted unless you are planning to sell your photo as fine art), so if you guys could get your members/classmates, etc to sign one of these (https://alumni.berkeley.edu/sites/default/files/Model-Release-Form.pdf) when needed that would be great.
 
Thank you in advance!
